Chris must care for an egg like it is a baby for a week as part of a social-studies project on parenting, but when Rochelle finds out that Chris was going to keep it in the refrigerator for the week, Chris finds out being a parent isn't as easy as it sounds; Tonya is afraid to sleep because Drew told her werewolves will come out in the dark, which explains the reason why the electric bill is $25.83 more than usual; Julius tries to find ways to lower the electric bill. Caruso puts Chris's egg on a chair, and Chris accidentally sits on it when he is about to be called up in class.

It is the last day of school, and Chris wants revenge on Caruso for making his life miserable. He puts cat food in the heating ducts and everywhere around the school causing Caruso to get blamed due to his love for cats. Meanwhile, Julius tries to fix Mr. Omar's clogged drain, but only makes things worse and gets reported to the housing authority. Drew teases Tonya causing his graduation to nearly end in disaster when Tonya throws an ice cream sundae on his cap and gown in retaliation. To make matters worse, Rochelle told him to not wear it until the graduation. In the end, Rochelle fixes the cap and gown with a pair of scissors and a well placed scarf.
